review_blob: 0.33L bottle. Barley and alcohol aroma. Hazy brown color with small beige top, stays. Overcooked sugar, grain, chestnut, syrup flavours. Quite strong alcohol taste. Interesting. Soft sugar, caramel mouthfeel.
0.5L bottle. Light barley wine aroma. Dark brown color with medium size beige foam on top, stays. Soft grain coffee, grain, light vanilla aroma. Light bitter. Nothing special.
0.33L Strong raisin and bread aroma. Dark brown color with massive beige foam on top. Quite strong flavour. Wood, prune, alcohol, black tea. Soft brandy flavour on finish. Alcohol mouthfeel.
O,4L bottle. Strong chemical banana aroma. Yellow color with medium size top. Dryed banana, mango flavor. Banana mouthfeel. Sugary. Interesting.
0.5L Bottle. Sweet barley wine aroma. Hazy apple juice appearance with tiny white top. Sweet honey, mouldy, stale malt flavours. Mild finish, low bitterness. Stale mouthfeel.
0.5L bottle. Honey and hop aroma. Pear, lemonade, light honey flavours. Bit watery finish. No bitterness.

0.33L bottle. Light chocolate and fruit aroma. Cloudy chestnut color with tiny white foam what is disappears for one moment. Sour, salty, caramel, lightly fruity flavours. Salty mouthfeel. Low bitterness. Toffee taste finish.
0.33L bottle. Soft and fruity aroma. Amber color with medium size hat, stays. Gentle IPA, lightly fruity and some herbs is felt somewhere. Sour mouthfeel. Medium bitterness. Mass beer feeling.
0.33L bottle. Mild, raisin bread aroma. Dark brown with tony beige head disappears for few seconds. Smoky, coffee, caramel flavours. Quite drinkable. Finish is bit watery and tasteless.
0.33L bottle. Baked beans, metallic aroma. Chestnut body with small white top. Very light flavours. Sour bad making kvass taste. Very booring.

0,33L bottle. Sweet and soft toffee aroma at first. Clear amber color with small white head, disappears for few minutes. Stale boiled water, light toffee, light rotten orange taste. Medium bitterness and beer is not so bad, but this is soft ipaish beer drink and not IPA.
O.5L bottle. Boiled egg, old stale wood aroma. Golden color with medium size white top what is vanishes for few seconds. Light alcohol, malt, pear taste. Some light bitterness on finish.
O.33L bottle. Mouldy, stale hop aroma. Pale yellow, pours fizzy, no foam. Corny pisswasser. Nothing to say.
0.33L bottle. Soft toffee and cocoa aroma. Dark brown body with brown medium size foam, disappears. Light cappuccino, toffee, vanilla, kvass flavours. Sticki mouthfeel. Light cocoa bitter finish.

0.33L bottle. Citric, egg, rotten potato aroma. Cloudy amber with massive beige hat on top, stays. Booring boiled vegetable start. In the middle something turns and taste goes nicely lemon seed bitter and feels like eating raw grapefruit. Very nice bitter taste stays after drinking. Pleasant citrus fruit, hop mix mouthfeel.
beer_name: Green Flash West Coast IPA (European Edition)

review_blob: 0.33L bottle. Nice strong Czech note hop and light coffee aroma. Clear golden color with small white top, disappears. Taste is quite strong and enjoyable. Nicely balanced. Very ok beer. Pleasant bitter hop mouthfeel. Very nice stylish blue bottle.

0.5L bottle. Caramel, lemon aroma. Clear brown color with tiny white head, disappears very quickly. Poor men IPA. Dry, raisin, caramel, brandy taste. Grapefruit peel mouthfeel after drinking is only good thing on this beer.

0.33L bottle. Light hop and white bread aroma. Pale yellow. Medium size white hat on top, disappears. Corn, vegetable soup, lightly malt felt somwhere. Quite reserved taste. Bit watery also. Bitterness is ok in finish, but that is not enough.

0.5L bottle. Grain and peas aroma. Clear golden color with fat white head, stays. Watery, light hop, corn and boiled potato water taste. Very booring. They tried to brew euro pale, but result is this. Shit!
0.5L bottle. Soft wheat aroma. Cloudy orange-amber color with massive fluffy foam on top. Fruity, banana, vanilla, fresh lemon juice, wheat flavours. Sour lemon taste mouthfeel.
0.5L can. Light toffee and hop aroma. Cloudy amber color with fat beige head, stays few minutes. Raisin, soft caramel, malt taste. Aftertaste disappears quickly. Low bitterness.
0.5L bottle. Barnyard, hop aroma. Clear orange color with massive beige foam, disappears quickly. Light caramel, sour malt, hay flavours. Medium bitter finish. Something is missing.

0.375L bottle. Light caramel, hop aroma. Black color with nice creamy beige foam, stays. Toffee, sour apple, very light smoke, salty, flavours. Soft and easy stout. Salty mouthfeel. Sour finish. Light bitterness.
0.375L bottle. Stale, metallic, hop aroma. Hazy yellow color with massive white foam, stays. Celler, malt, light yeast, metal flavours. Booring taste. Watery mouthfeel. Very quick finish.
0.5L can. Mouldy, barn, metal aroma. Clear yellow color with medium size white foam on top, stays. Stale, little sweet corn taste, light malt taste. Mouldy aftertaste. Low bitterness.
0.33L bottle. Booring hop aroma. Clear golden color, soft tiny white head. Simple table beer. Hop, malt and corn taste is represented. Watery and light taste. No bitterness, no soul.
0.47L bottle. Corn, light hop aroma. Light yellow color with medium size yellow top what is disappears very quickly. Sour watery shit. Like dishwater. Discusting.

0.5L bottle. Strong euro hop aroma. Yellow color with medium size white foam on top. Sweet, corny, malt is felt strongly. Not the worstest. Flavors are clearly highlighted. Malty aftertaste. Light bitter finish.

0.33L bottle @ R Kiosk. Cloudy, soft amber color with small foam on top. Alcohol, white bread, raisin aroma. Reminds home made beer, alcohol taste is quite strong, soft caramel. Strong alcohol mouthfeel.

0.33L bottle, batch 100. Something is rotten, orange peel aroma. Cloudy orange color with medium whit foam on top. Massive citrus, old stale vegetables, rubber flavours. Feels robust rotten fruits liquid. Nice bitter finish. Grapefruit seed mouthfeel.
0.33L bottle. Mouldy mandarin aroma. Cloudy amber color with medium size with small white foam. Plum juice, strong alcohol, raisin, sour lemon taste. Sour messy finish. Not for me.
0.33L bottle. Aroma is quite veggie and light white bread. Golden color with small white top. Corn, euro malt and hop taste. Nothing to say. Booring shit.
0.5L bottle. Nice citrus fruit and amarillo aroma. Dark golden color with medium size white hat. Generally is taste very ok, but it is very weak. Watery finish.
0.5L can. Metallic, euro hop aroma. Clear golden color with nice fluffy white foam. Corn, malt, alcohol, boiled potato flavours. Interesting light bitter finish.
0.33L bottle, batch 136. Sour raw lemon aroma. Hazy yellow color, whit small foam on top. Very citric, acid sour. Rotten orange, vegetable flavours. Sour finish also.

0.33L bottle. Cherry, cherry, cherry aroma. Dark pink-reddish color with medium size pink head, stays. I think it is natural cherry, raspberry flavour. Somewhere is overcooked sugar, but little. Enjoyable berry taste finish. Fresh and quality beer.
0.33L bottle, batch 6. Light black IPA aroma is felt. Coffee black color with tiny beige foam, stays. Kvass, roasted malt, light toffee, prune flavours. Medium bitter finish.

0.5L bottle. Mouldy celler and sweet canned corn aroma. Clear golden body and medium size white head, disappears. Sweet corn taste. Old undreground celler, potato, corn cyrup flavours. Very sweet and booring. Sticky mouthfeel.

0.33L bottle, batch 058. Roasted malt, garden berrys aroma. Nice black color with medium size reddish-brown foam on top. Caramellic-burned sugar, mild fresh cherry, roast, oil fried black bread flavours. Light smoke aftertaste. Roast and cherry mouthfeel. Nice one.
0.5L can. Light Czech and cheap euro hop mix, vomit aroma. Clear golden color with fluffy white head, disappears for 2 seconds. Watery Czech malt, corn, cognac flavours. Very watery finish. Shit.

0.33L bottle, batch 117. Belgian hop, red grape aroma. Clear reddish-brown color, medium foam on top. Soft caramel start, somewhere is typical belgian style, chestnut, flower taste. Light sour and bitter mouthfeel. Not my style.

0.33L bottle. Summer flowers and tropical fruits aroma. Hazy yellow color, tiny white hat on top. Floral, herbs, citrus fruits flavour. Some woman perfume aftertaste. Nice bitter finish. Interesting and not bad.
beer_name: Lervig Brewers Reserve White IPA Wit & IPA Fusion

review_blob: 0.33L bottle. Sour and fresh hop aroma and at the same time is sweet vegetabke taste. Cloudy golden color with medium size head, disappears. Taste is light. Carbonating coming up, lightly sweet malt flavour. Very light bitterness. Watery mouthfeel after drinking.

0.33L bottle. Light wheat, light fruit, like summer in coutryside aroma. Hazy orange color with tiny white head, stays. Fruity, yeast taste coming up and disappears same quickly, raw cerael, green peas, flavours. Actually peas mouthfeel stays a while after drinking. Easy summer beer and not bad.

0.33L bottle. Light smoke, burned bread aroma. Old motor oil colour. Small brown foam on top, disappears for few second. Overcooked sugar, over roasted bread, roasted malt, raisin, smoke, light vanilla, dark chocolate coming at finish. Very good. Hot chocolate mouthfeel.
0.33L bottle. Roasted white bread, light caramel aroma. Dark brown color, medium size foam on top, stays. Light herbs, roasted malt, black bread, cocoa, raisin flavours. Soft caramellic mouthfeel.
0.33L bottle, batch 114. Light yeast, grain aroma. Cloudy golden color with medium white foam on top. Sweetish lemonade, sour raw lemon juice, cereal flavours. Sour mouthfeel.
0.33L bottle, batch 113. Lightly sweet fruity aroma. Hazy orange color lot of little bubbles. Nice fat foam. Discreet APA taste. Pleasantly bitter. Little over carbonated. Nice grassy mouthfeel.

0.5L bottle. Fruity, yeast, wheat aroma. Light yellow body with nice clear white foam on top, disappears quickly. Yeast taste is quite strong with strong wheat, lightly fruity, banana, apple flavours. Soft finish. Yeasty mouthfeel.

0.33L bottle. Very light caramel, hop aroma. Deep copper color with medium size white foam on top. Looks nice, but taste is weak and light. Vegetable celler, rotten lemon, light toffee flavours. Light bitter finish.
